    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I know this was answered already, but I just ran into the same issue trying to specify the schema to use for the liquibase command line. </p>\n\n<p><strong>Update</strong>\nAs of JDBC v<a href=\"https://jdbc.postgresql.org/documentation/94/connect.html#connection-parameters\" rel=\"noreferrer\">9.4</a> you can specify the url with the new currentSchema parameter like so:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/mydatabase?currentSchema=myschema\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Appears based on an earlier patch:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20141025044151/http://postgresql.1045698.n5.nabble.com/Patch-to-allow-setting-schema-search-path-in-the-connectionURL-td2174512.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://web.archive.org/web/20141025044151/http://postgresql.1045698.n5.nabble.com/Patch-to-allow-setting-schema-search-path-in-the-connectionURL-td2174512.html</a></p>\n\n<p>Which proposed url's like so:\n</p>\n\n<pre><code>jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/mydatabase?searchpath=myschema\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 149455,
      "reputation" : 384,
      "user_id" : 361955,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96e1b0bfddfba5e81968059ca4623f09?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Scott Langley",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/361955/scott-langley"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1301514925,
    "creation_date" : 1301514925,
    "answer_id" : 5491562,
    "question_id" : 4168689,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>I submitted an updated version of a patch to the PostgreSQL JDBC driver to enable this a few years back.  You'll have to build the PostreSQL JDBC driver from source (after adding in the patch) to use it:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://archives.postgresql.org/pgsql-jdbc/2008-07/msg00012.php\">http://archives.postgresql.org/pgsql-jdbc/2008-07/msg00012.php</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://jdbc.postgresql.org/\">http://jdbc.postgresql.org/</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 68986,
        "reputation" : 23364,
        "user_id" : 200987,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 69,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1cdd96f59bb81a26d81870ba244215bc?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "oligofren",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/200987/oligofren"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1730979546,
      "post_id" : 26207054,
      "comment_id" : 139597007,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "To expand, setting the schema on Datasource will ensure the connection automatically gets <code>SET SESSION SCHEMA &#39;myschema&#39;</code>."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 109541,
      "reputation" : 4541,
      "user_id" : 290182,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4ed4ce7a63ebece709984db4a4d9703c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "beldaz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/290182/beldaz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1434743171,
    "last_edit_date" : 1434743171,
    "creation_date" : 1412542040,
    "answer_id" : 26207054,
    "question_id" : 4168689,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Don't forget <a href=\"http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.3/static/sql-set.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>SET SCHEMA 'myschema'</code></a> which you could use in a separate Statement</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>SET SCHEMA 'value' is an alias for SET search_path TO value. Only one\n  schema can be specified using this syntax.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>And since 9.4 and possibly earlier versions on the JDBC driver, there is support for the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/sql/Connection.html#setSchema(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>setSchema(String schemaName)</code></a> method.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 285794,
      "reputation" : 8928,
      "user_id" : 584670,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 69,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bdcd296b7d5e402ac2199f397fdc1107?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Steve",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/584670/steve"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 92,
    "last_activity_date" : 1708719317,
    "last_edit_date" : 1708719317,
    "creation_date" : 1424429873,
    "answer_id" : 28627332,
    "question_id" : 4168689,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As of version 9.4, you can use the <code>currentSchema</code> <a href=\"https://jdbc.postgresql.org/documentation/use/#connection-parameters\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">parameter</a> in your connection string.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/mydatabase?currentSchema=myschema\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
